A study found you should take pills with water, not coffee, juice or soda. And maybe not milk either. Anything other than water can affect how pills break down in your stomach. If it happens too fast, your body doesn't have enough time to absorb the meds.
Never Take Your Medication With This Drink, New Study Says | Eat This Not That
Even for non-prescriptions, a new study highlights one reason following your medication's instructions is essential to feeling better.
